WEBVTT

00:06.687 --> 00:09.155
<i>In New York City's
war on crime,</i>

00:09.222 --> 00:11.417
<i>the worst criminal offenders
are pursued</i>

00:11.491 --> 00:14.324
<i>by the detectives
of the Major Case Squad.</i>

00:14.394 --> 00:16.088
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:21.268 --> 00:25.102
We're short how much? Well,
throw in the red Bentley.

00:25.872 --> 00:28.466
That's right, baby,
out with the old.

00:29.343 --> 00:32.436
"Out with the old"? Is that
the theme of Friday's auction?

00:32.512 --> 00:35.481
Pam, we're celebrating
a life of privilege.

00:35.549 --> 00:37.881
With the magazine's circulation
declining, Mr. Merritt,

00:37.951 --> 00:40.385
some people say this
auction is about money.

00:40.454 --> 00:43.287
No, it's just my way
of sharing

00:43.357 --> 00:46.087
<i>40 years of good times
with the readers.</i>

00:47.494 --> 00:49.985
Jim, we're moving the breakfast
with the Teachers Union to next week.

00:50.063 --> 00:55.626
<i>Putting it all out there, baby.
The good, the bad, and the very bad.</i>

00:57.003 --> 00:59.563
<i>You, too, can own a piece of
George Merritt's good times,</i>

00:59.639 --> 01:01.607
<i>when 40 years of
Men's Privilege memorabilia</i>

01:01.675 --> 01:03.870
<i>goes up for auction
at Bartleby's.</i>

01:05.779 --> 01:08.270
All right, folks.
Let's get back to work.

01:08.348 --> 01:12.614
<i>My years as a Privilege Honey were
some of the happiest of my life.</i>

01:12.686 --> 01:16.850
I worked on the jet, you know.
That's where I met my husband Johnny.

01:17.090 --> 01:20.321
Is that what brought you all the
way from Houston, the memories?

01:20.394 --> 01:22.794
I owe Georgie Merritt so much.

01:22.863 --> 01:25.855
And if buying some of the wonderful
things he's putting up for sale

01:25.932 --> 01:27.991
helps him just
a teeny bit...

01:28.068 --> 01:29.194
Excuse me.
I'm sorry to bother you.

01:29.269 --> 01:30.293
That's all right.

01:30.370 --> 01:33.362
Are you Lila Brown,
the January, 1972 Honey?

01:33.974 --> 01:34.963
Yes, I am.

01:35.041 --> 01:37.509
This is...
I can't tell you.

01:37.577 --> 01:42.674
You had the most beautiful
hobbies. Would you sign this?

01:42.749 --> 01:44.512
Sure.

01:44.584 --> 01:47.018
You still got it, sugar.

01:48.221 --> 01:51.657
Lot 82. They actually
let me look through it.

01:51.725 --> 01:56.321
The estimate's eight grand.
Best money you'll ever spend.

01:58.098 --> 02:01.397
And we have $45,000 from
the lovely lady on the left.

02:01.468 --> 02:02.833
$45,000. Do I have
any advance on...

02:02.903 --> 02:03.927
50.

02:04.004 --> 02:07.633
Oh, $50,000 from Helen
on the telephone. $50,000.

02:07.707 --> 02:10.699
We have 50. $55,000
from the lady on the left.

02:10.776 --> 02:12.802
$55,000
60.

02:12.879 --> 02:15.109
$60,000 from Helen
on the telephone.

02:15.182 --> 02:17.980
$65,000 from the lovely lady
on my left. 65...

02:18.051 --> 02:19.075
70.

02:19.152 --> 02:22.121
$70,000 from Helen on the
phone. $75,000 from the lady...

02:22.189 --> 02:23.986
I'm sorry, sir, but the
bidder still has her paddle up.

02:24.057 --> 02:25.752
Helen, any advance?
No? $75,000...

02:25.826 --> 02:26.884
That's not possible, sir.

02:26.960 --> 02:27.949
Do you want to bid?

02:28.028 --> 02:30.019
Going, going, gone!

02:30.096 --> 02:31.290
I'm sorry, sir,
the bidding's over.

02:31.364 --> 02:32.888
Congratulations.

02:34.134 --> 02:36.125
And now we're gonna move
right along... Sir, I'm sorry.

02:36.203 --> 02:38.933
...to Lot Number 83.
Originally shoes...

02:39.005 --> 02:41.667
Sir, I have to hang up now.

02:42.676 --> 02:46.009
Sometimes it seems as if
it was all just yesterday.

02:46.079 --> 02:49.014
How about I take you all
downstairs for some hot chocolate?

02:49.082 --> 02:51.107
Now go, get your brother.

02:52.886 --> 02:55.514
Grandpa's taking us
for hot chocolate!

02:56.223 --> 02:59.681
The Hot Chocolate Express
is leaving the station!

03:06.900 --> 03:11.360
Johnny? What did you forget? Come
see what's become of your Honey.

